      },
      "date": "2011-03-22 08:49:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, approved\n\nNote that because of the change in struct obd_connect_data size, this patch needs to undergo interoperability testing with both 1.8 and 2.0.  I expect that it will work fine, because the code in ptlrpc_connect_client() was set up to allow this structure to grow in size, but it is always important to verify that practice matches theory.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "d82cfd33c272b39118d2bdce01c8347abf4a2ab5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2011-03-23 16:02:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\ntried following interoprability\n\nclient           server           result\n2.0(patched)     2.0              operable\n2.0              2.0(patched)     server complains client's obd_connect_data buffer too small    \n-----------------------------------------------------------\n1.8(patched)     1.8              client complains server's obd_connect_data reply buffer too small\n                                  (ptlrpc_connect_interpret():Wrong connect data from server)\n1.8              1.8(patched)     server complains client's obd_connect_data buffer too small",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
