    {
      "id": "3dc980fb37de798103e42cd9a3f9524d1230f2c4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-21 06:34:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nI have two questions.\nFirst, is not max_bytes a per-file property on ext3/4? Depends on extent use?\n\nSecond question, I assume ext3-based ldiskfs still retains the 2T limit?\nIf so then we have data-corruption looming for the case where somebody upgrades ext3 ldiskfs to ext4 ldiskfs I think, since old limit was in fact 2T-4k which means once the limit is lifted, some very large files at the edge of the old limit would get some extra zeroes inserted close to the end?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "7455a2a8b07eb2f2bc85e4bc72a854d6ac676d30",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 103,
        "name": "Zhenyu Xu",
        "email": "bobijam@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bobijam"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-23 01:52:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\n>First, is not max_bytes a per-file property on ext3/4? Depends on extent use?\n>Second question, I assume ext3-based ldiskfs still retains the 2T limit? If so then we have data-corruption looming for the case where somebody upgrades ext3 ldiskfs to ext4 ldiskfs I think, since old limit was in fact 2T-4k which means once the limit is lifted, some very large files at the edge of the old limit would get some extra zeroes inserted close to the end?\n\nmax_bytes affect file's lli->lli_maxbytes, and if part of OST upgrade, the lsm_max_bytes won't be expanded, since it confines to the miminum max file size limit. And the lli_maxbytes limit just confines what the upper bound a writing to file can reach, I don't quite understand what would make extra zeroes appended to old limited file, can you shed a light? Thanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "9698b38e55b71d3ff7184437965cde4f68341da2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-23 03:33:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nSo...\nI was thinking of the case where there the object extend all the way to the current limit (2T-4k).\nFor simplicity, if we assume there are 2 objects and and stripe size is 64k, that means first object will extend all the way to 2T-4k, but that means last chunk would only be 60k.\nBut now that I think more about it, might be this is fine.\nAttempt to extend the object beyond max size would not cause it to overflow to a different object but instead would just generate and error and so we are fine.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
